# 2025-07-08 05:46:15.313679
+TASK: 
+You are a senior full-stack engineer and product designer. Your job is to create a complete, production-grade web application that replicates the core features and user experience of DocuSign, enhanced with generative AI capabilities for document automation.
+
+PROJECT NAME: 
+DocuSign AI Clone
+
+OBJECTIVE: 
+Build a secure, scalable, and user-friendly web platform for electronic signatures, document automation, and workflow management, with AI-powered document analysis and generation.
+
+---
+
+## Functional Requirements
+
+1. **User Authentication & Roles**
+   - Secure registration and login (email/password, OAuth, SSO)
+   - User roles: Admin, Sender, Signer, Viewer
+
+2. **Dashboard**
+   - Overview of pending, completed, and in-progress documents
+   - Quick actions: Upload, Send, Sign, Track
+
+3. **Document Upload & Preparation**
+   - Upload documents (PDF, DOCX, images)
+   - Drag-and-drop field placement (signature, initials, date, text, checkbox)
+   - AI-powered field detection and auto-tagging
+
+4. **AI Document Analysis & Generation**
+   - Use generative AI to:
+     - Analyze uploaded agreements for risks, missing clauses, or compliance issues
+     - Summarize and explain contract sections in plain language
+     - Generate new contracts or templates based on user input
+
+5. **Signature Workflow**
+   - Route documents to multiple signers with custom order and roles
+   - Email/SMS notifications for signers
+   - Real-time status tracking and reminders 6. **E-Signature & Audit Trail**
+   - Legally binding e-signature capture (draw, type, upload)
+   - Tamper-evident document storage
+   - Complete audit trail (who viewed/signed, when, IP address)
+
+7. **Template Management**
+   - Save reusable document templates
+   - AI-assisted template creation and field mapping
+
+8. **Integration & API**
+   - REST API for external integration
+   - Webhooks for status updates
+   - Connectors for Google Drive, Dropbox, Salesforce, etc.
+
+9. **Compliance & Security**
+   - Encryption at rest and in transit
+   - Compliance with ESIGN, UETA, eIDAS, GDPR
+   - Role-based access control and activity logging
+
+10. **Admin Panel**
+    - User management, usage analytics, billing, and audit logs
+
+---
+
+## Technical Requirements  **Frontend:** React (with TypeScript), responsive design, drag-and-drop UI for document prep
+- **Backend:** Node.js (Express or NestJS), REST API, WebSocket for real-time updates
+- **Database:** PostgreSQL (for users, documents, audit logs), S3-compatible storage for files
+- **AI Integration:** OpenAI API (or similar) for document analysis, summarization, and generation
+- **E-Signature:** PKI-based digital signature implementation
+- **Security:** JWT authentication, HTTPS, input validation, rate limiting
+- **Deployment:** Dockerized, with Docker Compose for multi-service orchestration
+
+---
+
+## User Stories
+
+- As a user, I can upload a contract and have AI auto-detect fields for signature and initials.
+- As a sender, I can specify the signing order and assign roles to each participant.
+- As a signer, I receive a secure link to review and sign documents from any device.
+- As an admin, I can view analytics on document usage and manage users.
+- As a user, I can generate new contracts by describing my needs in plain language, and the AI creates the draft.
+
+---
+
+## UI/UX Requirements
+
+- Clean, modern interface inspired by DocuSign
+- Step-by-step document sending wizard
+- Mobile-friendly and accessible (WCAG 2.1 AA)
+- Real-time feedback and notifications
+
+---
+
+## Output Instructions
+
+- Scaffold the project structure for frontend and backend.
+- Generate sample code for key modules: authentication, document upload, AI integration, signature workflow, and audit logs.
+- Provide sample database schema (PostgreSQL).
+- Include Dockerfile and docker-compose.yml for local development.
+- Write clear documentation for setup, API, and deployment.
+- Suggest best practices for security, compliance, and scalability.
+
+---
+
+**If any requirement is ambiguous, make reasonable assumptions and flag them for review. Focus on modular, maintainable, and production-ready code and architecture.**
+

